### English Title:
Egyptian Government Decides to Increase Fuel Prices

### English Text Summary:
The Egyptian government has announced an increase in fuel prices, effective from Friday, marking the first increase in 2025 and the second in six months. This decision aligns with the government's plan to completely lift fuel subsidies and adjust prices to match global rates as part of an economic reform program in collaboration with the International Monetary Fund. The increase has sparked widespread outrage on social media, especially as users noted the contrast with declining global oil prices. The price hikes include an increase of two Egyptian pounds per liter for various types of gasoline and diesel. The government aims to eliminate fuel subsidies by the end of 2025, except for diesel and gas cylinders. The announcement has raised concerns about inflation and the impact on the cost of living.

